covered: GET Method: Valid Request scenarios cover standard retrievals with default and parameterized inputs.
Query Parameters: Comprehensive coverage of offset, limit, and audit values, including invalid and edge cases.
Pagination: Tests validate different pagination scenarios including default limit, explicit offset/limit, and empty results when out of range.
Empty Response: No bundles scenario returned as an empty JSON array (TC06).
Authorization: Unauthorized access tested (401) to verify authentication failure handling.
Error Handling: Various invalid parameter combinations (400/422), service unavailability (503), and timeouts (504) covered.
Security: SQL injection attempt scenario tested (TC14).
Performance: Tests measure response times under normal load and peak load (TC17, TC18).
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Tests ensure audit MINIMAL with offset 0 and no-audit param behavior (TC19, TC20).
State Variation: Partially populated databases tested (TC21).
Edge Cases: Extra parameters ignored (TC15); boundary int values tested (TC16).
Data Shape: Response is a JSON array of Bundle objects as per specs (TC01, TC03, TC04).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling/limit on requests (e.g., 429).
Caching Behavior: No tests validating ETag/Cache-Control headers.
403 Forbidden scenario: Only 401 tested; absence of explicit 403 coverage.
Limit=0 edge case: No test for zero limit behavior.
Additional 5xx error paths beyond 503/Timeouts beyond 504 not covered.
Last-page/page-count verification: No explicit test verifying total pages or last page semantics across dataset sizes.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests and check for 429 responses under heavy load.
Add caching header validation tests (ETag and Cache-Control) and caching invalidation behavior.
Add tests for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions scenarios alongside 401.
Add tests for limit=0 to clarify API behavior with zero items per page.
Add tests for 500 Internal Server Error path to ensure robust server error handling.
Add tests to verify total page counts and last-page behavior across dataset sizes, including validations of total_count when available.
